TEXT 328 -296 Left 4 ;Zero crossing detector
TEXT 1064 -72 Left 2 ;How it works:\n \n1. The rectifier rectifies the input AC.\n2. The positive half waves, as long as they are higher than 10V push curren through the phototransistor pulling the output low.\n3. When the positive half waves go lower than 10V the phototransistor shuts down and the output goes high.\n \nNotes:\n1. Can be used with high voltages.
